# Supabase

- All schema changes via `supabase/migrations/*.sql` — never edit prod in the dashboard
- After migrations: `generate_typescript_types` (MCP) or `supabase gen types typescript --local`
- Apply locally: `supabase db reset` (optional; needs Docker)
- Apply remote: `apply_migration` (MCP) or `supabase db push` (CLI) — **agent runs this**
- RLS must enforce auth server-side; client checks are UX only

## Agent-owned Supabase ops (do not defer to user)

Use **Supabase Cursor Plugin** (`plugin-supabase-supabase`) or CLI with `SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN`:

- `create_project` — new dev/staging projects (after `get_cost` / `confirm_cost`)
- `apply_migration` — push committed SQL to a project ref
- `get_publishable_keys` / `supabase projects api-keys` — populate `.env.local`
- Auth config — Management API or dashboard only if MCP/API unavailable
- `list_migrations`, `get_advisors`, `execute_sql` — verify and debug

Never ask the user to create a project or paste URL/keys you can fetch. See [`.cursor/rules/mcp-first-ops.mdc`](mcp-first-ops.mdc).

## Gitignore (CLI-generated paths)

The Supabase CLI writes local state under `supabase/.temp/` (linked project ref) and `supabase/.branches/` (branch metadata). These must stay **gitignored** — never commit them.

Root `.supabase/` (Docker local stack data) is also gitignored. When adding Supabase CLI features or other stack tools, extend `.gitignore` in the same PR and verify with `yarn check:requirements`.
